Collection: The Centre for Architectural Conservation-Riwaq Collection
Series: The Centre for Architectural Conservation-Riwaq Sub-collection 1: Photographs
Title: درج باب العامود في القدس
AltTitle.other: The Damascus Gate Stairs
Description.note: Taken in 1981, this black-and-white photograph shows the Damascus Gate stairs and Hindiyeh Building, where most lawyers and doctors opened their offices such as Dr Subhi Ghusheh and where ʿumair Daʿnah was also commonly seen selling newspapers. 150 years old, Schmidt's Building, where the Schmidt's School was opened, is seen to the right of the photograph.|~|درج باب العامود في القدس ويظهر في الصورة عمارة هندية حيث كانت مكاتب الاطباء والمحاميين من امثال الطبيب صبحي غوشة، وكان عمير دعنا يقف تحت العمارة يبيع جرائده. وعلى اليمين تظهر أجزاء من عمارة الشمت التي احتوت مدرسة الشمت وعمرها أكثر من 150 سنة
References: Asad, Hamza, "The Riwaq- Centre for Architectural Conservation Collection," archival inventory, May - June 2018, the Palestinian Museum Digital Archive.; Khaldun Bshara (Director of Riwaq Centre for Architectural Conservation), interview with PMDA researcher Hamza Asad, non-transcript, 2019, the Palestinian Museum Digital Archive.
Subject topic: Culture and Arts|~|Architecture and Landscape|~|Social History
Series & Collection: The Centre for Architectural Conservation-Riwaq Collection  | The Centre for Architectural Conservation-Riwaq Sub-collection 1: Photographs
Description (Eng): Taken in 1981, this black-and-white photograph shows the Damascus Gate stairs and Hindiyeh Building, where most lawyers and doctors opened their offices such as Dr Subhi Ghusheh and where ʿumair Daʿnah was also commonly seen selling newspapers. 150 years old, Schmidt's Building, where the Schmidt's School was opened, is seen to the right of the photograph.
Description (Ara): درج باب العامود في القدس ويظهر في الصورة عمارة هندية حيث كانت مكاتب الاطباء والمحاميين من امثال الطبيب صبحي غوشة، وكان عمير دعنا يقف تحت العمارة يبيع جرائده. وعلى اليمين تظهر أجزاء من عمارة الشمت التي احتوت مدرسة الشمت وعمرها أكثر من 150 سنة

AltTitle.other: An RPPC of a Wrecked, Antiquated House in Majdal Shams, Issued by the Arab Association for Development, 1994
Description.note: Issued by the Arab Association for Development, this real photo postcard (RPPC) shows an antique house in Majdal Shams village, the Occupied Golan Heights; it was wrecked during the June 1967 War. |~|صورة غير ملونة، وهي بطاقة بريدية لبيت قديم قصف في حرب الـ 1967 في مجدل شمس بالجولان السوري، من انتاج الجمعية العربية للتنمية بمناسبة مرور 27 عام على احتلال الجولان السوري.
References: Asad, Hamza, "The Riwaq- Centre for Architectural Conservation Collection," archival inventory, May - June 2018, the Palestinian Museum Digital Archive.; Khaldun Bshara (Director of Riwaq Centre for Architectural Conservation), interview with PMDA researcher Hamza Asad, non-transcript, 2019, the Palestinian Museum Digital Archive.
